  "title": "Encoding Richness and Retrieval",
  "concept": "Your brain stores information by linking it to the sensory and motor activity that happened during learning—more channels firing during encoding means more pathways to retrieve the memory later.",
  "interactiveId": "2d5c5313-d3c0-4c2d-956e-bf96fdf55f51",
  "sourcePieceId": "74f8d228-c871-4991-9315-82be7f26cb34",
  "publishedAt": 1778422016890,
  "voiceScore": 90,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Encoding Richness and Retrieval</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --accent: #c9a227;\n    --channel-active: #1a6b62;\n    --channel-inactive: #d4d0c8;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--channel-active);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 1ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .channels {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));\n    gap: 12px;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n  }\n  .channel {\n    padding: 12px;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    background: #fff;\n    transition: all 220ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .channel.active {\n    border-color: var(--channel-active);\n    background: #f0faf8;\n  }\n  .channel-name {\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    margin-bottom: 6px;\n  }\n  .channel.active .channel-name {\n    color: var(--channel-active);\n  }\n  .channel-bar {\n    height: 8px;\n    background: var(--channel-inactive);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  .channel-bar .fill {\n    height: 100%;\n    width: 0%;\n    background: var(--channel-active);\n    transition: width 220ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .channel.active .channel-bar .fill {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 12px 14px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .pathways {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 8px;\n    margin-top: 8px;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n  }\n  .pathway {\n    display: inline-block;\n    padding: 4px 10px;\n    background: var(--line);\n    border-radius: 12px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    transition: all 180ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .pathway.lit {\n    background: var(--channel-active);\n    color: #fff;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .channels {\n      grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Add sensory channels during learning</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Each channel that fires during encoding becomes a pathway for retrieval later.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"channels\">Active channels:</label>\n  <input id=\"channels\" type=\"range\" min=\"1\" max=\"5\" value=\"1\" step=\"1\" aria-describedby=\"channels-out\">\n  <output id=\"channels-out\" for=\"channels\">1</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"channels\">\n  <div class=\"channel\" data-channel=\"1\">\n    <div class=\"channel-name\">Visual</div>\n    <div class=\"channel-bar\"><div class=\"fill\"></div></div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"channel\" data-channel=\"2\">\n    <div class=\"channel-name\">Motor</div>\n    <div class=\"channel-bar\"><div class=\"fill\"></div></div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"channel\" data-channel=\"3\">\n    <div class=\"channel-name\">Spatial</div>\n    <div class=\"channel-bar\"><div class=\"fill\"></div></div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"channel\" data-channel=\"4\">\n    <div class=\"channel-name\">Tactile</div>\n    <div class=\"channel-bar\"><div class=\"fill\"></div></div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"channel\" data-channel=\"5\">\n    <div class=\"channel-name\">Context</div>\n    <div class=\"channel-bar\"><div class=\"fill\"></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  <strong>Retrieval pathways:</strong> <span id=\"pathway-count\">1</span>\n  <div class=\"pathways\" id=\"pathways\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">One channel firing during learning means one way to find the memory later.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('channels');\n    var channelsOut = document.getElementById('channels-out');\n    var pathwayCount = document.getElementById('pathway-count');\n    var pathwaysContainer = document.getElementById('pathways');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n    var channelEls = document.querySelectorAll('.channel');\n\n    var pathwayLabels = [\n      'seeing the shape',\n      'the hand motion',\n      'where it was on the page',\n      'how the surface felt',\n      'what else was happening'\n    ];\n\n    function update() {\n      var count = +slider.value;\n      channelsOut.textContent = count;\n      pathwayCount.textContent = count;\n\n      // Activate channels up to count\n      for (var i = 0; i < channelEls.length; i++) {\n        if (i < count) {\n          channelEls[i].classList.add('active');\n        } else {\n          channelEls[i].classList.remove('active');\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Build pathway chips\n      pathwaysContainer.innerHTML = '';\n      for (var j = 0; j < pathwayLabels.length; j++) {\n        var chip = document.createElement('span');\n        chip.className = 'pathway';\n        if (j < count) chip.classList.add('lit');\n        chip.textContent = pathwayLabels[j];\n        pathwaysContainer.appendChild(chip);\n      }\n\n      // Update caption\n      if (count === 1) {\n        caption.textContent = 'One channel firing during learning means one way to find the memory later.';\n      } else if (count === 2) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Two channels firing means two pathways—if one fails, the other might still work.';\n      } else if (count === 3) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Three active channels triple your retrieval routes. The memory becomes easier to find.';\n      } else if (count === 4) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Four channels create a dense network. Multiple cues can trigger the same memory.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'Five channels firing means five ways to access what you learned. Richly encoded information is hard to lose.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
